cs.CR, cs.CY, cs.DS, cs.SE, cs.DB 

This paper primarily focuses on the analysis of ransomware campaigns and their economic impact from a Bitcoin transactions perspective. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also involves the use of data analysis and classification techniques, which could fall under cs.CY (Computers and Society) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Additionally, the paper presents a framework for identifying and analyzing Bitcoin addresses, which could be categorized under cs.SE (Software Engineering) and cs.DB (Databases).
